The paper proposes an adversarial imitation learning algorithm for control tasks, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of model-based planning and model-free learning also suggests a focus on reinforcement learning and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the use of visual inputs in some of the experiments suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and the use of planning algorithms suggests a possible connection to control systems (cs.SY).
